snippet.title: Kim Kardashian: Instagram's No. 1 enemy?
snippet.description: A report suggests that Instagram's most popular user, Kim Kardashian, is raving mad about the site's policy changes. Might she leave? Might she take all her followers with her?

snippet.title: At Apple, gold iPhone 5S is known as 'the Kardashian phone'
snippet.description: No, it didn't merely have some secret code name with numbers and letters. Apparently, the (relatively) blingiest of the iPhones was associated from the beginning with, well, a lack of taste.

snippet.title: Kardashian mom chooses Twitter to reveal baby pic
snippet.description: In a move that must make Facebook feel a touch ill, Twitter is yet again at the center of the world's attention. Well, who would ever watch "Keeping Up With The Syrians"?

snippet.title: Kardashian, Banks, Bieber (Who isn't trying to profit on tech?)
snippet.description: As Kim Kardashian has put her name to a celebrity video game and Tyra Banks invests in an app that puts pretty pictures on lock screens, we only wait for Bill Murray to launch a "Lost In Translation" iPhone app.

snippet.title: Apps to help you get pregnant
snippet.description: Several smartphone apps are designed to help couples conceive. CNET's Kara Tsuboi reports on how they work and what fertility experts say is the best way to use them.

snippet.title: Kanye to sue YouTube founder for posting Kardashian proposal video?
snippet.description: A report suggests Kanye West is furious someone posted a video of his proposal to Kim Kardashian. That someone is said to be YouTube founder Chad Hurley, who posted 150 seconds to his new MixBit site.

snippet.title: Searching for Kim Kardashian
snippet.description: Google's e-book store is coming soon, Santa can leave you a personalized message on Google Voice, and Kim Kardashian is one of the most popular search terms of 2010 on both Yahoo and Bing.

snippet.title: Kim and Kanye sue, accuse YouTube founder of being failure
snippet.description: After rumors emerge that the happy couple is unhappy with Chad Hurley for pushing footage of their proposal onto his new site, a lawsuit is filed.

snippet.title: Kim Kardashian dominates Bing searches in 2010
snippet.description: There should be few surprises in this year's top Bing searches. People continue to search for celebrity news, political figures, and apparently even free stuff from Walmart.

snippet.title: Huh? Kanye's birthday gift from Kim was... Woz?
snippet.description: The Apple co-founder and iconic rapper get together for a chat about their shared interest in technology.
